Spicy root & lentil casserole
Method
Heat the oil in a large pan and cook the onion and garlic over a
medium heat for 3-4 minutes until softened, stirring occasionally.
Tip in the potatoes, carrots and parsnips, turn up the heat and cook
for 6-7 minutes, stirring, until the vegetables are golden.
Stir in the curry paste or powder, pour in the stock and then
bring to the boil. Reduce the heat, add the lentils, cover and simmer
for 15-20 minutes until the lentils and vegetables are tender and the
sauce has thickened.
Stir in most of the coriander, season and heat for a minute or
so.Top with yogurt and the rest of the coriander. Serve with naan
bread.
Ingredients
2 tbsp sunflower or vegetable oil
1 onion, chopped
2 garlic clove, crushed
700g potatoes, peeled and cut into
chunks
4 carrot, thickly sliced
2 parsnip, thickly sliced
2 tbsp curry paste or powder
